# Section A – Complete System Architecture
## AI-Based ECD Decision Support Layer for India (ICDS / WD&CW Alignment)

---

## A.1 High-Level Architecture – Layered Description

The system is decomposed into six horizontal layers. Each layer has a defined responsibility boundary and communicates only through specified interfaces.

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  LAYER 6 – GOVERNANCE & ANALYTICS TIER                              │
│  State Dashboard │ CDPO View │ Supervisor View │ Audit Log Console  │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  LAYER 5 – ROLE-BASED ACCESS & PRESENTATION TIER                    │
│  AWW Android App │ Web Portal (Supervisor/CDPO/State)               │
│  JWT + RBAC Gateway │ Session Management                            │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  LAYER 4 – API & ORCHESTRATION TIER                                 │
│  REST API Gateway │ Queue-Based Async Jobs │ Sync Conflict Manager  │
│  Webhook Dispatcher │ Audit Event Emitter                           │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  LAYER 3 – INTELLIGENCE TIER                                        │
│  Risk Engine │ Developmental Trajectory Engine │ Explainability Mod │
│  Calibration Service │ FN Mitigation Monitor │ Cohort Aggregator    │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  LAYER 2 – DATA MANAGEMENT TIER                                     │
│  PostgreSQL (Structured) │ TimescaleDB (Time-series trajectories)   │
│  Encrypted Object Store │ Consent Registry │ Audit Ledger DB        │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  LAYER 1 – EDGE / OFFLINE TIER                                      │
│  Android App (Local SQLCipher DB) │ Offline Risk Engine (ONNX)      │
│  Encrypted Local Cache │ Sync Queue │ Conflict Resolver (device)    │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> All computation layers operate within government-controlled infrastructure. No third-party cloud tenancy is used. Models run on-premise or on NIC/MeitY-compliant government cloud (GI Cloud / NIC empanelled data centres).

---

## A.2 Component Breakdown

### A.2.1 Edge / Offline Layer Components

| Component | Technology | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| Android Data Capture App | Kotlin, Jetpack Compose | ASHA/AWW-facing form capture, offline screening |
| Local Encrypted Database | SQLCipher (AES-256) | Stores records offline when network unavailable |
| On-Device Risk Engine | ONNX Runtime (Android) | Runs quantized screening model **without connectivity** (provisional tier only — see A.6) |
| Sync Queue Manager | WorkManager + Room | Queues changes, manages retry and backoff |
| Conflict Resolver (Client) | Last-Write-Wins + field-level merge | Resolves offline edits before server sync |
| Local Consent Store | Encrypted SharedPreferences | Stores signed consent tokens per child record |

### A.2.2 API & Orchestration Layer Components

| Component | Technology | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| REST API Gateway | FastAPI (Python) or Spring Boot | Exposes versioned REST endpoints; validates tokens |
| Auth Service | Keycloak (on-prem) | OAuth2 + OIDC; RBAC role enforcement |
| Async Job Queue | Celery + Redis | Handles trajectory recalculation, report generation |
| Sync Conflict Manager (Server) | Custom reconciliation service | Resolves conflicts from multiple offline devices |
| Audit Event Emitter | Kafka or direct DB write | Emits tamper-evident audit log entries |
| Webhook Dispatcher | Celery beat | Notifies upstream systems (e.g., ICDS-CAS integration) |

### A.2.3 Intelligence Layer Components

| Component | Technology | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| Risk Engine | Scikit-learn / XGBoost / LightGBM | Produces risk tier: Low/Medium/High/Critical per domain |
| Developmental Trajectory Engine | Custom Python service + TimescaleDB | Tracks longitudinal scores, computes trajectories |
| Explainability Module | SHAP (SHapley Additive exPlanations) | Per-prediction feature contributions in plain language |
| Calibration Service | Platt Scaling / Isotonic Regression | Ensures probability outputs are calibrated |
| FN Mitigation Monitor | Threshold adjustment + alert rules | Reduces false-negative rate for High/Critical tiers |
| Cohort Aggregator | SQL + Pandas batch jobs | Block/district-level impact metrics |
| Retraining Orchestrator | MLflow + Airflow (scheduled) | Manages model versioning, drift detection, retraining |

### A.2.4 Data Management Layer Components

| Component | Technology | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| Primary Relational DB | PostgreSQL 15+ | Child records, assessments, users, consents |
| Time-Series DB | TimescaleDB (PostgreSQL extension) | Trajectory data, longitudinal screening time points |
| Encrypted Object Store | MinIO (on-prem, S3-compatible) | Model artifacts, PDF reports, training datasets |
| Consent Registry | Separate PostgreSQL schema | Auditable consent capture and revocation records |
| Audit Ledger | Append-only PostgreSQL table + checksum chain | Tamper-evident audit trail |

### A.2.5 Governance & Analytics Layer Components

| Component | Technology | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| AWW View | Android App embedded dashboard | Individual child list, risk flags, referral actions |
| Supervisor View | React Web App | Block-level aggregates, intervention status, alerts |
| CDPO View | React Web App | District-level analytics, cohort trends, reports |
| State Dashboard | React Web App + Metabase/Superset | Statewide indicators, coverage, programme fidelity |
| Audit Log Console | React Admin Panel | Immutable log viewer, export, compliance review |

---

## A.3 Data Flow Diagram – Explanation

### Primary Flow: Child Screening (Online)

```
AWW captures screening data via Android App
    │
    ▼
App validates locally → submits to API Gateway (HTTPS/TLS 1.3)
    │
    ▼
Auth Service validates JWT + role = AWW
    │
    ▼
API Gateway writes raw assessment to PostgreSQL (encrypted at rest)
    │
    ▼
Async Job: Risk Engine invoked → produces (score, tier, SHAP values)
    │
    ▼
Risk result written to DB; trajectory engine updates longitudinal record
    │
    ▼
Audit Event Emitter logs: [user, action, timestamp, record_id, data_hash]
    │
    ▼
Risk tier surfaced to AWW App on next poll / push notification
    │
    ▼
Supervisor/CDPO dashboards aggregate results via batch cohort jobs
```

### Secondary Flow: Offline Screening (Disconnected AWW)

```
AWW captures data → stored in local SQLCipher DB
    │
On-device ONNX Risk Engine produces provisional risk tier
    │
Result stored locally with sync_status = PENDING
    │
On connectivity restoration: WorkManager triggers sync
    │
Client-side conflict resolver checks record timestamps + version hashes
    │
Sync payload submitted to API (compressed, encrypted)
    │
Server Conflict Manager applies reconciliation policy
    │
Server Risk Engine re-runs on server-authoritative data
    │
Canonical result returned; local record updated with sync_status = SYNCED
    │
Audit log records sync event with device_id, timestamp delta
```

### Governance Flow: Audit & Compliance

```
Every data write/read/delete → Audit Event Emitter
    │
Append-only audit table: (event_id, user_id, role, action, table_ref,
record_id, old_hash, new_hash, timestamp, IP/device)
    │
Checksums chained: each entry's hash includes previous hash (ledger chain)
    │
Audit Log Console: read-only view for authorised compliance officers
    │
Scheduled export: monthly signed PDF audit summary → State officer inbox
```

---

## A.4 API Structure Outline

All APIs are versioned under `/api/v1/`. Authentication is Bearer JWT. Role enforcement is at the gateway level.

### Authentication & Session
| Method | Endpoint | Role | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| POST | `/api/v1/auth/token` | All | Exchange credentials for JWT |
| POST | `/api/v1/auth/refresh` | All | Refresh access token |
| POST | `/api/v1/auth/logout` | All | Revoke session |

### Child Records
| Method | Endpoint | Role | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| POST | `/api/v1/children` | AWW | Register new child record |
| GET | `/api/v1/children/{id}` | AWW, Supervisor | Retrieve child record |
| PATCH | `/api/v1/children/{id}` | AWW | Update child record (versioned) |
| GET | `/api/v1/children` | Supervisor, CDPO | List children (paginated, filtered) |

### Screening Assessments
| Method | Endpoint | Role | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| POST | `/api/v1/assessments` | AWW | Submit new screening assessment |
| GET | `/api/v1/assessments/{id}` | AWW, Supervisor | Retrieve assessment + risk result |
| GET | `/api/v1/assessments/child/{child_id}` | Supervisor | Longitudinal assessment history |

### Risk Engine
| Method | Endpoint | Role | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| GET | `/api/v1/risk/{assessment_id}` | AWW, Supervisor | Retrieve risk tier + SHAP explanation |
| POST | `/api/v1/risk/batch` | Internal | Batch recalculation (admin-triggered) |

### Trajectory
| Method | Endpoint | Role | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| GET | `/api/v1/trajectory/{child_id}` | Supervisor, CDPO | Full developmental trajectory |
| GET | `/api/v1/trajectory/cohort` | CDPO, State | Cohort-level trajectory aggregates |

### Consent
| Method | Endpoint | Role | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| POST | `/api/v1/consent` | AWW | Capture signed consent for child |
| GET | `/api/v1/consent/{child_id}` | Supervisor | Retrieve consent record |
| DELETE | `/api/v1/consent/{child_id}` | Supervisor | Revoke consent (triggers data hold) |

### Sync (Offline Client)
| Method | Endpoint | Role | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| POST | `/api/v1/sync/push` | AWW (device) | Push pending offline records |
| GET | `/api/v1/sync/pull` | AWW (device) | Pull server-authoritative updates |
| GET | `/api/v1/sync/status` | AWW (device) | Check sync queue status |

### Analytics & Reports
| Method | Endpoint | Role | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| GET | `/api/v1/analytics/block` | Supervisor | Block-level risk distribution |
| GET | `/api/v1/analytics/district` | CDPO | District-level metrics |
| GET | `/api/v1/analytics/state` | State Officer | Statewide programme indicators |
| GET | `/api/v1/reports/export` | CDPO, State | Generate and download report (async) |

### Audit
| Method | Endpoint | Role | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| GET | `/api/v1/audit/logs` | Compliance Officer | Query audit log (filtered, paginated) |
| GET | `/api/v1/audit/export` | Compliance Officer | Export signed audit log |

